<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-10-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="498" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Starbuck</persName>,
                                    district attorney, to Mr. <persName type="to">Soar</persName>,
                                    Attorney-General.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Office of United States
                                        Attorney</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Salem, North
                                        Carolina</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-10-11"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 11,
                                1869</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><seg type="margin">[179]</seg>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your letter concerning the steamer Hornet, detained in
                                the port of Wilmington, *and the case will soon undergo an
                                investigation before the United States commissioner, which I trust
                                will develop the true character of the vessel; then such proceedings
                                will be instituted as the facts may warrant.</p>
                            <p>I am, sir, very respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>D. H. STARBUCK,<lb/><hi rend="italic">United States
                                        Attorney.</hi></signed>
                            </closer>
                            <postscript>
                                <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">E. R. Hoar</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Attorney-General.</hi></p>
                            </postscript>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>